==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liquid air
<hw>Liq"uid air</hw>. <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A transparent limpid
liquid, slightly blue in color, consisting of a mixture of liquefied
oxygen and nitrogen. It is prepared by subjecting air to great pressure
and then cooling it by its own expansion to a temperature below the
boiling point of its constituents (N: -194⟦deg⟧ C; O: -183⟦deg⟧
C.).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liquidambar</ent>⟦br⟧
